{
  "stem": "27285.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Anna did not survive, neither did her son, Paul, and they perished in Poland.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was on my mother's side.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "From my father, I remember only his mother, which was the second wife, I think, of his father.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because his father, my grandfather, I never knew.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I only knew about him because he was like a [INAUDIBLE] in Berlin, of all the places.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Leopold Hofmeister, but he went under the name of Paulie [?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Hoffer. ?] And he always married the first ladies, so later on in Terezin, I met about three-- [LAUGHS] three females who were--",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--grandmothers, but-- now my only grandmother died, as well.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But the name Hofmeister was not so common, so whenever it popped up you knew it was some connected to me.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, in Vienna, of course.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In Vienna we lived in-- we lived in the second district, which was called, the Mazzesinsel, like the island of Matzo, [LAUGHS] because it was very Jewish.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And there was a big great synagogue.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I remember only an uncle, [INAUDIBLE], who did those little beautiful hand-scissored flags, or something, for the [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I remember the synagogue, but we were not specially religious, but we were very Jewish.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "School was very nice, as long as I went there.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I went like for two classes.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I didn't even finish.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was a public school, not a Jewish school-- public school, but I was a very-- very interested in learning.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was a great thing for me to do.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I was very heartbroken when, in the second class, I didn't get all those good grades because, as they said, Hitler was already there, and Jewish kids are not supposed to be good pupils.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I didn't so [INAUDIBLE] because I could not comprehend it.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
